zany slice of his ever-more public personality had made him faster.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI just want to get this going,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she said, smiling, in a way that indicated she knew more than she wanted to say out loud.\\u00c2  Just before he left for Paris, Lyles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s biomechanist Ralph Mann told him one thing: He held the thumb and pointer finger on his right hand no more than half an inch apart.\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 900, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 401, \"end\": 405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah's_Ark\", \"score\": 0.797264841449554, \"rank\": 0.25428834538980843, \"text\": \"Noah\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah's_Ark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah's_Ark\"}, {\"begin\": 752, \"end\": 757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.985039847984927e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 782, \"end\": 792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Mann\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ralph Mann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Mann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Mann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A sliver maybe.\", \"from\": 901, \"to\": 916, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The end of a pen cap.\", \"from\": 917, \"to\": 938, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A popsicle stick, laid flat.\", \"from\": 939, \"to\": 967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 100-meter final, Mann predicted, would bethat close\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094specifically, the physical non-distance between first place and second.\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 1097, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 989, \"end\": 993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man\", \"score\": 0.9999978203646713, \"rank\": 2.1745562845160783e-06, \"text\": \"Mann\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles, 27, nearly tied the 100-meter final on Sunday.\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1099, \"end\": 1104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9890789083176801, \"rank\": 0.011011849229328411, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He came as close as one can in his sport to runningexactlythe same time as another sprinter.\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1245, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Five-thousandths of a single second separated the gold and silver medal winners.\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1326, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s0.005seconds.\", \"from\": 1327, \"to\": 1348, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Google: what can happen in 0.005 seconds?\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1390, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The primary and prevalent answer is \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6nothing.\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1438, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At least that can be perceived.\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1470, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In winning the 100-meter dash, Lyles secured his first\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094but not likely his last\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 1472, \"to\": 1574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1503, \"end\": 1508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9890789083176801, \"rank\": 0.011011849229328411, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt feels good,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he said, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cto back it up.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  A lifetime unfolded between the walk onto the track andthe photo finish.\", \"from\": 1576, \"to\": 1700, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It began with an extraordinary Olympic prelude.\", \"from\": 1701, \"to\": 1748, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The inside of the stadium all but pulsated.\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1792, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A deejay, clad in a black leather jacket, wearing sunglasses at night, spun deep house.\", \"from\": 1793, \"to\": 1880, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the bright stadium bulbs went completely dark, without warning, the lights along the upper ring flashed white and purple, in sync with the beats.\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 2029, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The crowd gasped.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2047, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Spotlights scanned from one side to the other, while tiny lights sparkled throughout the stands, thanks to wristbands fans were given at the gates.\", \"from\": 2048, \"to\": 2195, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The thumping bass elevated, slowly at first, then faster, faster and faster, until the whole stadium felt like a bubble of anticipation about to pop.\", \"from\": 2196, \"to\": 2345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One by one, the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100-meter finalists made their way onto the track.\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here they were, in Paris, in an Olympic final, in their sport\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s premier race.\\u00c2\\u00a0 Jamaica\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Kishane Thompson, a favorite with the world\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s fastest time this year, leaned back in the entrance tunnel, before slowly raising both arms, tilting his head back and roaring like a lion.\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2441, \"end\": 2446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.985039847984927e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2524, \"end\": 2532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9433582282181211, \"rank\": 0.060042696493459426, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The camera strung above the purple track dropped and elevated, slinging left and right, before settling on the obvious suspect: Lyles.\", \"from\": 2704, \"to\": 2838, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t saunter onto the track.\", \"from\": 2840, \"to\": 2875, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nor did he swagger in.\", \"from\": 2876, \"to\": 2898, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Heran.\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 2905, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not sprinting, but not slowly.\", \"from\": 2906, \"to\": 2936, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t stop at the starting blocks, like everybody else.\", \"from\": 2937, \"to\": 2998, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He cruised about 15 meters beyond the others.\", \"from\": 2999, \"to\": 3044, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles never stopped moving, like he had bottled every ounce of energy and online hatred and unrealized ambition but could no longer hold it in.\", \"from\": 3046, \"to\": 3189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His feet bounced on the purple track\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094purple, his favorite color\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094springing up, then down, as if guided by a trampoline underfoot.\", \"from\": 3190, \"to\": 3322, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fred Kerley, another American finalist, entered the stadium right then.\", \"from\": 3324, \"to\": 3395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3324, \"end\": 3335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fred Kerley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\"}, {\"begin\": 3345, \"end\": 3353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9996437145375378, \"rank\": 0.00018008143769176595, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He held a finger to his lips, as if to say,quiet down.\", \"from\": 3396, \"to\": 3450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps that gesture was meant for Lyles, whose general nature had grated on his competition, especially over the last six months.\", \"from\": 3451, \"to\": 3581, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3486, \"end\": 3491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9890789083176801, \"rank\": 0.011011849229328411, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles screamed.\", \"from\": 3583, \"to\": 3598, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He beat his chest with both hands.\", \"from\": 3599, \"to\": 3633, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Energy seemed to rise from his body, like steam rising from a whistling kettle.\", \"from\": 3634, \"to\": 3713, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He saluted, then appeared to repeat the same three words, over and over.\", \"from\": 3714, \"to\": 3786, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It looked like he was saying:Thank you,God.\", \"from\": 3787, \"to\": 3830, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The crowd began to clap.\", \"from\": 3832, \"to\": 3856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The introductions dragged on for minutes that unspooled like hours.\", \"from\": 3857, \"to\": 3924, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The competitors\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094the world\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s fastest men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094stepped in place, swayed, danced, waiting for the signal.\", \"from\": 3925, \"to\": 4028, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The defending Olympic 100-meter champion, Lamont Marcell Jacobs of Italy, stood still with his eyes closed.\", \"from\": 4029, \"to\": 4136, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4078, \"end\": 4092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marcell Jacobs\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\"}, {\"begin\": 4096, \"end\": 4101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9767900910054914, \"rank\": 0.023690049151373082, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 9:53 p.m. local time, the sprinters leaned their bodies forward and placed their spikes into the starting blocks.\", \"from\": 4138, \"to\": 4254, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The stadium dropped into near silence.\", \"from\": 4255, \"to\": 4293, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The loudest sound came from the helicopters hanging overhead.\", \"from\": 4294, \"to\": 4355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anticipation isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t the right word.\", \"from\": 4357, \"to\": 4393, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The general feeling landed aroundstart this damn thing already.\", \"from\": 4394, \"to\": 4457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The gun sounded.\", \"from\": 4458, \"to\": 4474, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And off they went.\", \"from\": 4475, \"to\": 4493, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the first few meters, Lyles sprinted from the back of the pack\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094perhaps, even, in last place.\", \"from\": 4495, \"to\": 4593, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4521, \"end\": 4526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9890789083176801, \"rank\": 0.011011849229328411, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t last long.\", \"from\": 4594, \"to\": 4622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He caught them, all of them, these strong, powerful, human locomotives, each churning as fast as humanly possible toward the same line down the track.\", \"from\": 4623, \"to\": 4773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For a second, it appeared that Kerley had won.\", \"from\": 4775, \"to\": 4821, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then it appeared that Lyles did.\", \"from\": 4822, \"to\": 4854, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4844, \"end\": 4849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9890789083176801, \"rank\": 0.011011849229328411, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then Thompson.\", \"from\": 4855, \"to\": 4869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4860, \"end\": 4868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9433582282181211, \"rank\": 0.060042696493459426, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those three names flashed across the video screens, in that order.\", \"from\": 4870, \"to\": 4936, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone stood around the finish line.\\u00c2  Lyles approached Thompson at one point.\", \"from\": 4937, \"to\": 5017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4995, \"end\": 5003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9433582282181211, \"rank\": 0.060042696493459426, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cHey, man,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Lyles told him, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI think you got it.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  It didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t take long for officials to come back with the results.\", \"from\": 5018, \"to\": 5143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5034, \"end\": 5039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9890789083176801, \"rank\": 0.011011849229328411, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles surely must have never been happier to be dead wrong.\", \"from\": 5144, \"to\": 5203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Those same three names flashed on those same screens, only this time, in a different order: Lyles-Thompson-Kerley.\", \"from\": 5204, \"to\": 5318, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100-meter final gold, silver and bronze medalists, respectively.\\u00c2  In the video analysis Olympic officials distributed after the race, Lyleswas last, even at the 30-meter mark.\", \"from\": 5319, \"to\": 5507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He did not lead at any other point.\", \"from\": 5508, \"to\": 5543, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Lane 7, he didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t have time to look left, at Thompson in Lane 4, or Kerley in Lane 3.\", \"from\": 5544, \"to\": 5634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5594, \"end\": 5602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9433582282181211, \"rank\": 0.060042696493459426, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He told himself the obvious, in fractions of critical seconds.I need to lean.\", \"from\": 5635, \"to\": 5712, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s what Lyles did.\", \"from\": 5713, \"to\": 5740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5730, \"end\": 5735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9890789083176801, \"rank\": 0.011011849229328411, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Heleaned.\", \"from\": 5741, \"to\": 5750, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They all did.\", \"from\": 5751, \"to\": 5764, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Photographs from the finish line make the runners look like their necks are being bent forward by a gale-force wind.\", \"from\": 5765, \"to\": 5881, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His winning time, 9.79 seconds, matched Ben Johnson\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s steroid-aided world record in 1988, the one that didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t stand.\", \"from\": 5883, \"to\": 6003, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He is the first male U.S. sprinter to win the race since Justin Gatlin in 2004.\", \"from\": 6004, \"to\": 6083, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles began to alternately gallop and jog and walk around the track.\", \"from\": 6084, \"to\": 6152, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He pumped his fists.\", \"from\": 6153, \"to\": 6173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He unleashed screams.\", \"from\": 6174, \"to\": 6195, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He held his race bib, the one that read LYLES in black letters, and jumped a barrier to celebrate with Keisha and other relatives.\", \"from\": 6196, \"to\": 6326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6299, \"end\": 6305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keisha_Buchanan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keisha\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keisha_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keisha_Buchanan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles showed up asNoahon Sunday.\", \"from\": 6328, \"to\": 6360, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last month, Keishasaid that the biggest difference she saw in her son from Tokyo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094where he won bronze in the 200 meters\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and Paris, was a fuller embrace of just how different he was.\", \"from\": 6361, \"to\": 6545, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6488, \"end\": 6493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.985039847984927e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He came to a better understanding of self, which led him to a better understanding of his sport.\\u00c2  Before Paris, former sprinter Michael Johnson said that of all America\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s promising young superstars, Lyles had the best chance to vault to a new level of stardom with his results.\", \"from\": 6546, \"to\": 6826, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6652, \"end\": 6657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.985039847984927e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, 